  "explanation": "The defendant, acting in a position of trust as an accountant, committed a serious breach of fiduciary duty by embezzling $25,000. While the lack of a prior criminal record and the partial repayment of funds are significant mitigating factors demonstrating remorse and a lower risk of recidivism, the nature of the crime requires a period of incarceration to serve as a deterrent and to reflect the gravity of the betrayal of the employer-employee relationship. The unauthorized outburst from the spectator has been disregarded in this determination, as sentencing is based strictly on legal principles and the specific facts of the case.",
  "verdict": 6
}
